If in a Woman with Child, the Dugs are liable to Inflamation, Tumors, and 
                        lcers;
                     In a woman that lies in. much more are they o in a Child-bed Woman, and one that gives uck, by reaon of the curdling of her Milk. Diocorides writes, That the welling of the Dugs is brought down, by the application of bruied Hemlock, which Experience hews to be true. Howbeit, Dodonaeus approves not of this Medicine, by reaon of the malignant, and venemous Nature of this Herb, which being applied unto the Dugs, may wrong the Heart.

When the Trunk is come as far as the Claves it produces the Mammaria or Dug-Vein, which is twofold; 
                  T. 12. f. 1. c c.  internal and external: they are both carried throughMammaria


the Longitude of the breat-bone unto the Dugs. But the internal being the greater, having tranmitted a branch through an hole in the Breat-bone, into the Dugs, Runs along unto the Right or treight Mucle, that it may Joyn it elf to the Epigatrica. Hippocrates was wont to open the external, in Inflamation and pains of Parts belonging to the Chet: But now becaue of the Obcurity of thoe Veins, that operation is not of ue: intead whereof Hor-leeches may be applied, or Cupping-Glaes with Scarrification.

